name: bottom-navigation

description: A python program to measure the speed of different cryptographic functions using PyCryptodome.

name: group-messenger
description: Group text messaging Android app. Implements a modified version of the ISIS algorithm in order to provide Total and FIFO ordering guarantees while effectively handling device failures.

name: handwriting-comparison
description: This project finds the similarity between the handwriting samples of the known and the unknown writers by using three machine learning approaches (linear regression, logistic regression and neural networks). Used the CEDAR "AND" training dataset which contains set of input features for each handwritten "AND" sample.

name: handwritten-digit-recognition
description: Classification system for identifying handwritten digits using an ensemble model of logistic regression, neural networks, SVM and random forest.

name: homography
description: Implementing Panorama (Image Warping) in python using OpenCV

name: simple-amazon-dynamo
description: Dynamo styled distributed key-value storage in Android with simultaneous availability and linearizability guarantees. Key design techniques include concurrent read and write operations, quorum replication, failure handling, per-key linearizability, object versioning, consistent hashing (similar to Chord DHT) and gossiping.

name: simple-chord-dht
description: Simple distributed hash table based on Chord. Key design techniques include ID space partitioning/re-partitioning, ring-based routing and node joins.

name: traffic-light-simulation
description: A simulation of a moving car, encountering traffic lights at random distances in Unity
